      "message": "strictly speaking all comments like that should start with \"\u003ca thing being commented\u003e \u003cverb\u003e ...\"\n\nE.g. \n\n\"chown changes ownership of a path\"\n\nhttps://github.com/golang/go/wiki/Comments\n\nThis is not strictly necessary for non-exported symbols (lowercase ones), but it is very-very encouraged for publicly exported symbols. This makes docs look more consistent.",
