      "writtenOn": "2017-09-22T00:58:28Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "it would be really great if we can inline all these templates into the executable itself, so to deploy this stuff we need only to deploy the executable\n\nWe have a tool that can do this: https://godoc.org/go.chromium.org/luci/tools/cmd/assets\n\nExample usage: https://chromium.googlesource.com/infra/luci/luci-go/+/master/server/settings/admin/internal/assets/generate.go\n\n(We may need to do a slight adjustment to the tool to recognize template files: https://chromium.googlesource.com/infra/luci/luci-go/+/master/tools/cmd/assets/main.go#39)\n\nSo:\n1. Drop generate.go file with the \"go:generate ...\" incantations.\n2. cd into your package directory and run \"go generate .\"\n3. It will produce a file assets.gen.go with all templates hardcoded into *.go. They will become available through generated function GetAsset, like this one: https://godoc.org/go.chromium.org/luci/server/settings/admin/internal/assets#GetAsset\n4. Teach substituteFile to use GetAsset to grab a template instead of ReadFile.",
